data.title: The Art of Computer Programming, Volume 1, Fascicle 1
data.meta_description: This book covers the internal machine language of MMIX, a mythical computer which is very much like nearly every general-purpose computer designed since 1985. The language is powerful enough to allow brief programs to be written for most algorithms.
